    <note>Liu(2) Guangshi [7046] Yaoren's [1250] father. His family's hereditary occupation was the military officer corps. He accompanied Zhao(1) Gaozong [9010] as a commander (Zhizhi shi) during the move south and subsequently served as a general under Han(2) Shizhong [8050] and Zhang(1) Jun [211]. Xiang(2) Zizhang's son-in-law. Father-in-law of Zhang(1) Ji(3)'s [7151] father, Congyuan(a) [3166]. His wife was buried in Qiantang county (Hangxian), therefore identification of new residence. Liu Yizhi, WJ, 50.5b-8b (wife, born Xiang, whi died in 1151 at age 63). CBD, 5, 3942-3.</note>
